<strong>(Genesis)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;An extraordinary journey.&#8221;<br />
—<em>Irish Times</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260434" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/thomas-pynchon-marisa-meltzer-chris-kraus-and-more-24-new-books-out-today/attachment/9780385551113/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9780385551113.jpeg" data-orig-size="296,450" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Hole in the Sky, Daniel H. Wilson" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9780385551113-197x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9780385551113.jpeg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-260434" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9780385551113-197x300.jpeg" alt="Hole in the Sky, Daniel H. Wilson" width="197" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9780385551113-197x300.jpeg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9780385551113-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9780385551113-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9780385551113.jpeg 296w" sizes="(max-width: 197px) 100vw, 197px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Daniel H. Wilson, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780385551113" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Hole in the Sky</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Doubleday)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Not only a thrilling, brilliant page-turner, its pages also turned me into the kind of reader I always want to be &#8230; The kind of reader who can’t stop reading, who dreads the book coming to an end even while I can’t stop making my way toward it.&#8221;<br />
—Tommy Orange</p>
