<strong>(Knopf)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Banville is at his Jamesian finest in this beguiling novel of diabolical gambits.&#8221;<br />
—<em>Booklist</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260414" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/thomas-pynchon-marisa-meltzer-chris-kraus-and-more-24-new-books-out-today/version-1-0-0-54/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9781541606234.jpeg" data-orig-size="323,500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Version 1.0.0&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Version 1.0.0&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9781541606234-194x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9781541606234.jpeg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-260414" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9781541606234-194x300.jpeg" alt="Taylors Version, Stephanie Burt" width="194" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9781541606234-194x300.jpeg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9781541606234-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9781541606234-32x50.jpeg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9781541606234.jpeg 323w" sizes="(max-width: 194px) 100vw, 194px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Stephanie Burt, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781541606234" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Taylor&#8217;s Version</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Basic Books)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Burt not only articulates the force of Swift&#8217;s songwriting genius, but—perhaps more importantly—makes the case for her place in the literary tradition. A provocative, sharp, well-argued book for any Taylor Swift fan—or skeptic.&#8221;<br />
—Carmen Maria Machado</p>
