<strong>(Knopf)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Compelling and timely &#8230; A sobering but ultimately empowering read providing a clear-eyed look on recent history and a call to plan wisely for the pandemics of tomorrow.&#8221;<br />
—<em>Library Journal</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260425" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/thomas-pynchon-marisa-meltzer-chris-kraus-and-more-24-new-books-out-today/71f9ayg8wrl-_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/71f9Ayg8wRL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="The Natural Order of Things, DOnika Kelly" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/71f9Ayg8wRL._UF10001000_QL80_-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/71f9Ayg8wRL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-260425" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/71f9Ayg8wRL._UF10001000_QL80_-200x300.jpg" alt="The Natural Order of Things, DOnika Kelly" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/71f9Ayg8wRL._UF10001000_QL80_-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/71f9Ayg8wRL._UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/71f9Ayg8wRL._UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/71f9Ayg8wRL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 667w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></p>
